NAME
       ls - list directory contents

SYNOPSIS
       ls [-aAlh1] [FILE ...]

DESCRIPTION
       Lists the contents of each FILE, or of the current directory if
       none is given. By default produces a short multi-column listing
       and hides entries starting with a dot.

OPTIONS
       -a    show hidden entries, including . and ..
       -A    show hidden entries except . and ..
       -l    long format with mode, size, and name
       -h    print sizes in human-readable form (with -l)
       -1    force one entry per line

EXAMPLES
       ls
       ls -la /etc
       ls -1 /bin

SEE ALSO
       find(1), stat(1), cat(1)
